data.name: Azure App Service (Web Apps)
data.description: View and monitor the primary metrics of Azure App Service (Web Apps).

markdown.markdownText:
**UseCases Covered:**

* **Health & Availability:**
    * Health Check Status (overall & per instance)
    * Instance Count (scale events and availability)
* **Application Performance & Traffic:**
    * Request Count (total & by instance)
    * Response Time (average & per instance)
    * Bytes Sent & Received (totals & by instance)
    * App Connections (active connections per instance)
* **Compute & Memory Usage:**
    * CPU Time (total, by instance, and day-over-day)
    * Memory Usage (average & per instance)
    * Private Bytes (per instance memory footprint)
* **Garbage Collection (GC):**
    * Gen0, Gen1, Gen2 GC Counts (overall & by instance)
* **I/O Metrics:**
    * I/O Read/Write/Other Bytes/Operations per Second
* **Functions – Load & Execution:**
    * Current Functions Loaded
    * Function Execution Count & Rate
    * Function Duration (per function & over time)

More about performance monitoring of Azure App Service (Web Apps) [here](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-monitor/reference/supported-metrics/microsoft-web-sites-metrics)
